t69.text: The ‘essential services frontline’ (as being described by social media and mass media) is actually our species’ last line of defense. Thanks for coming to my TEDtalk.

t70.text: The greatest fallacy of the statement in question is believing that YOU (the soldier in this war) can go about living your pre-war civilian life believing you have an ironclad defense against the enemy that is attacking us. Nope. You’re at war. You’re the FRONTLINE.

t71.text: This means that YOU (each and everyone of us) must take up arms and fight our own instincts and ways of life because that is the exploit the enemy uses. Your weapons are clear: Maintain physical distancing, good hand hygiene, and staying at home and bunkering down because...

t72.text: This means that the idea that our “essential workers are our frontlines against this common enemy” is a flawed statement. A critical error in knowing our enemy in a planet-scale war. Following the comparison to a physical war, the frontlines are YOU: The People.

t73.text: But in this war, the rules of engagement are different. The enemy has weaponised US: our lifestyles, and our societal habits as a whole. The attack is not so much directed towards a front, but more an exponential cascade seeded from WITHIN the bastions (the ‘frontlines’ protect).

t74.text: The objective of whom it is to mount multiple lines of defense (form a front) to prevent the progress of the opposing force and subsequent fall of the representative civilisation/bastion/banner of Whatever.

t75.text: But if you draw parallels to a physical battle in a war, the front-line are often the soldiers/units that face first enemy contact. These are the brave men and women that have the troubling yet patriotic duty to protect and to serve the rest of the population (by definition)

t76.text: Make no mistake, if you are part of the human species, a planet-scale war is being waged between 2 species: humans vs a virus. As with all wars, the troops will be determined by the enemy at hand. So the comparison to the “front-line” is not too far fetched (dr, nrses etc)
